issue.title: Document the current set of supported datalog rules
issue.body:
I've started a doc here:  https://github.com/atomisthq/docs/blob/main/docs/authoring/datalog/rules.md

https://docs.atomist.services/authoring/datalog/rules/

I think we should close on a few things

- [ ] need a better `string-matches?` predicate - do we have one?
- [ ] `is-in-docker-org?` private?
- [ ] is `skill-config-value` private?  Should users use `get-skill-config-value`?
- [ ] should config-value-tx be able to watch for a set of parameter changes to make it more generic?

commits.message:
Add exposed-ports to mirror https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#expose (and set creationTime) (#17)

* Set creation time to "now"

* Add `exposed-ports` to mirror https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#expose

A seq of either numbers or strings are accepted.

If strings, they follow the Docker format.

The config key is this:

```
{:exposed-ports [80 "53/tcp"]}
```

forkee.name: pod-babashka-fswatcher
forkee.description: Babashka filewatcher pod.

issue.title: On windows, classpath in image uses backslash as file separator
issue.body:
When jibbit is used from windows, the classpaths used in the image will have backslashes instead of slashes in the file paths. This yields the following error when the image is run:
```
Error: Could not find or load main class clojure.main
Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: clojure.main
```

I believe that the problem is this line: https://github.com/atomisthq/jibbit/blob/350da0bb44eb965f7a7e6f01a444e92257b90c1e/src/jibbit/core.clj#L84

If I replace `:from-working-dir` there with `:docker-path` things work as expected. 

I can provide a pull request if you'd like.

comment.body: @jjttjj thanks - seems like a good change.  I'll take a look in the am.
